/* Notepad++ HexEditor — Hebrew (he)
 *
 * Full translation. Keys mirror Localizable.en.strings; comments stay in
 * English so future translators can diff against the canonical source.
 *
 * Format specifiers (%1$@, %1$d, %1$zu, %1$lu, %2$@, etc.) are preserved
 * verbatim. The "N⁠o⁠t⁠e⁠p⁠a⁠d⁠+⁠+" form embeds U+2060 Word Joiners and
 * must be copied byte-for-byte from the English source.
 *
 * GitHub URLs are hard-coded — only the surrounding label text is
 * translated.
 *
 * RTL note: Hebrew is right-to-left. The plugin pins its hex view
 * (offset / hex bytes / ASCII grid) and the Options dialog form content
 * to LTR regardless of locale — hex dumps are universally read LTR even
 * by Hebrew/Arabic developers. Menus, NSAlert dialogs, and the host
 * Notepad++ chrome flip to RTL automatically. See LOCALIZATION.md.
 */

